name: Illinois

processing_metadata.description: Official Illinois DMV processing rules and validation requirements

global_rules.code_system: Illinois uses code numbers: 31=Apportioned, 35=Disabled/Handicapped, 44=Disabled Vanity, 46=Passenger Vehicle, 57=Semi Trailer, 77=B Truck
global_rules.character_restrictions: Illinois DOES NOT MIX ALPHA and NUMERIC CHARACTERS together on their License Plates. This applies to all plates including PERSONALIZED plates.
global_rules.processing_note: Processing rules vary by plate type and are defined in the CSV matrix. Custom processing types will be provided separately.
global_rules.passenger_format: Passenger plates MUST have a SPACE separating letters from the numbers (Ex: MARY 124)
global_rules.passenger_pickup_format: Passenger Pickup Truck plates are the same, EXCEPT the NUMERIC CHARACTERS come before the ALPHA CHARACTERS (Ex: 124 MARY)
global_rules.personalized_format: Personalized plates can have ALL ALPHA or ALL NUMERIC CHARACTERS

processing_metadata.character_modifications: Allows letter O on personalized plates

plate_type.description: Letter O allowed on personalized plates

processing_metadata.processing_description: Select 'Apportioned Plate' from Plate Type drop-down for all Illinois plates that display 'Apportioned' on them.

processing_metadata.visual_identifier: WHEELCHAIR SYMBOL will appear on the LEFT side of the plate
processing_metadata.special_instructions: Will contain only NUMERIC CHARACTERS. Both Disabled/Handicapped and Disabled Vanity plates will have the wheelchair logo on Left. When they are not all numeric – they are considered Disabled Vanity plates.
processing_metadata.processing_description: Select 'Disabled/Handicapped Plate' from the Plate Type drop-down when you see an Illinois plate with the WHEELCHAIR symbol and the characters are ALL NUMERIC.

processing_metadata.visual_identifier: WHEELCHAIR SYMBOL will appear on the LEFT side of the Plate
processing_metadata.special_instructions: Will contain ALL ALPHA or ALPHA-NUMERIC CHARACTERS
processing_metadata.processing_description: Select 'Disabled Vanity Plate' from the Plate Type drop-down when you see the wheelchair symbol and the characters are ALPHA or ALPHA-NUMERIC.
Select 'Passenger Vehicle' from the Plate Type drop-down. ALL Illinois plates that were not previously mentioned will be considered 'Passenger Vehicles'.

processing_metadata.visual_identifier: 'ST' will appear VERTICALLY on the RIGHT side of the plate
processing_metadata.special_instructions: Any trailer plate other than Apportioned or Semi-Trailer will be considered a Passenger Vehicle plate. 'ST' MUST BE KEYED!
processing_metadata.processing_description: Select 'Semi Trailer Plate' from the Plate Type drop-down when you see the letters 'ST' vertically stacked on Illinois plates.

processing_metadata.character_modifications: The letter 'B' MUST BE MANUALLY ADDED AT THE END OF THE PLATE # displayed
processing_metadata.visual_identifier: 'B TRUCK/B' will appear on the RIGHT side of the plate
processing_metadata.special_instructions: You must MANUALLY KEY the letter 'B' at the END of the plate. Example: 3107003B
processing_metadata.processing_description: Select 'B Truck' Plate Type from the drop-down when you see the letter 'B' following the plate number or 'B TRUCK' displayed vertically on the right side of plate.
Select 'Passenger Vehicle' from the Plate Type drop-down. ALL Illinois plates that were not previously mentioned will be considered 'Passenger Vehicles'.
processing_metadata.special_instructions: You must KEY the letters "AM" at the END of the plate number. Example: 000000AM or 797002AM. If the vehicle is a clearly marked Emergency Vehicle, REJECT the image using the "Emergency Vehicle" reject code.
